---

<BaseLayout
  title="8-Day Grand Safari | Go Kilimanjaro Treks"
  description="Eight-day grand Tanzania safari with extended game viewing across all major parks."
  schemas={schemas}
>
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="page-hero-eyebrow">Tanzania Safari Itinerary</span>
    <h1>8-Day Grand Safari.</h1>
    <p>Eight-day grand Tanzania safari with extended game viewing across all major parks.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Request a Quote &#x2192;</a>
      <a href="https://wa.me/255677917500" class="btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&#x1F4AC; WhatsApp Nelson</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">8 Days / 7 Nights Tanzania Wildlife &amp; Migration SafariFrom the Savannah of Tarangire to the Great Migration of Northern Serengeti</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Starting From USD 3,250 Per Person*Rates depend on season, accommodation category, and group size.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 1: Arrival in Tanzania - Welcome to Arusha</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon arrival at Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO), you will be warmly welcomed by your professional safari guide and transferred to your accommodation in Arusha, the vibrant gateway to Tanzania's northern safari circuit.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Nestled beneath the slopes of Mount Meru, Arusha provides the perfect introduction to East Africa's wildlife adventures. The remainder of the day is reserved for relaxation, allowing you to settle in and prepare for the exciting journey ahead.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: River Trees Inn</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: HB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 2: Tarangire National Park - The Land of Giants</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, depart for Tarangire National Park, a remarkable wilderness famous for its giant baobab trees and some of the largest elephant populations in East Africa.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As you explore the park, enjoy sightings of elephants, lions, giraffes, zebras, wildebeests, buffaloes, and numerous bird species. The Tarangire River attracts wildlife throughout the year, creating exceptional opportunities for game viewing in one of Tanzania's most scenic landscapes.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Following an exciting day in the bush, continue to your lodge for dinner and overnight.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Country Lodge Karatu</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 3: Makuyuni Wildlife Area - Untouched Wilderness Experience</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, continue your safari to the beautiful Makuyuni Wildlife Area, a lesser-known gem offering authentic wildlife encounters away from the more crowded parks.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This vast landscape is characterized by rolling plains, acacia woodlands, and seasonal wildlife corridors connecting several important ecosystems of northern Tanzania. During your exploration, keep watch for zebras, giraffes, antelopes, elephants, and various bird species that inhabit this natural wilderness.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">The peaceful surroundings and stunning scenery provide a unique opportunity to experience Tanzania's wild beauty in its purest form.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Country Lodge Karatu</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 4: Central Serengeti - Into the Endless Plains</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Today your journey continues toward the world-famous Serengeti National Park. Traveling through the beautiful Ngorongoro Highlands, enjoy breathtaking views and glimpses of traditional Maasai communities along the way.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon entering the Serengeti, the landscape unfolds into endless golden plains stretching beyond the horizon. Begin your first game drive in Central Serengeti, one of the most wildlife-rich regions of the park, known for its year-round predator activity.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Expect encounters with lions, leopards, cheetahs, elephants, buffaloes, and large herds of grazing animals roaming freely across the savannah.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Baobab Tented Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 5: Northern Serengeti - Following the Great Migration</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, continue north through the Serengeti ecosystem toward one of Africa's most celebrated wildlife destinations.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Northern Serengeti is renowned for its remote wilderness, breathtaking landscapes, and seasonal migration activity. Vast herds of wildebeests and zebras gather in this region as they follow ancient migratory routes toward the Mara River.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Spend the afternoon exploring this remarkable area while searching for predators and witnessing the incredible movement of wildlife across the plains.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Enkutoto Migration Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 6: Northern Serengeti - The Mara River Experience</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a full day exploring the spectacular Mara River region, one of the highlights of the Great Migration.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Here, thousands of wildebeests gather along the riverbanks before attempting dramatic crossings through crocodile-inhabited waters. These unforgettable moments showcase one of nature's greatest survival spectacles.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Beyond the migration, the region offers exceptional opportunities to observe lions, leopards, cheetahs, elephants, and numerous other species thriving within this vast ecosystem.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Optional hot-air balloon safaris are available for guests seeking a unique aerial perspective of the Serengeti.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Enkutoto Migration Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 7: Ngorongoro Crater - Africa's Wildlife Paradise</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After a final morning safari experience in Serengeti, depart for the Ngorongoro Conservation Area.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Descend into the magnificent Ngorongoro Crater, the world's largest intact volcanic caldera and one of Africa's most extraordinary wildlife sanctuaries. The crater floor supports an impressive concentration of wildlife including lions, elephants, buffaloes, hippos, hyenas, and the rare black rhino.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a picnic lunch surrounded by breathtaking scenery before ascending the crater walls and continuing to your lodge for a relaxing evening.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Manyara Best View Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 8: Departure - Farewell to Tanzania</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a leisurely breakfast while taking in the beautiful views of the Great Rift Valley and surrounding highlands.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Afterwards, begin your journey back to Arusha. Depending on your flight schedule, a short stop for shopping or local experiences may be arranged before your transfer to Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO).</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As you depart Tanzania, you carry with you unforgettable memories of spectacular wildlife encounters, breathtaking landscapes, and the timeless beauty of Africa's most celebrated safari destinations.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: BB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">END</p>
  </div>
</section>

